prefectures.description_english: Went to Kanazawa for the second stop of my Hokuriku trip. Overall, I'd say it's a nice mix of city and culture, I like it quite a bit. Maybe a little too much promotion of gold leaf products though.

prefectures.description_english: My first stop in the Hokuriku portion of my trip. I felt like the buildings in the main station area had personality and it was convenient getting around. Tojinbo was definitely the highlight.
Despite actively avoiding snowy places for the longest time, I finally went to Takayama. Thankfully there wasn't much snow around.

Stayed here for a week to rest after going to so many different places in a short period. Was in Matsuzaki, which is a small town in the south-western portion of the Izu Peninsula. It's a quaint town with good food and very friendly people.
I stopped at Nagoya Station three times, but each time we only stopped for lunch.

prefectures.description_english: Went here on a day trip from Kyoto. I was pretty tired so I didn't get to see many places, but, to be honest, the places that I did go to didn't wow me too much.
The first day trip from Kyoto was to here. The deer are extremely fun to watch and the nature is beautiful.

Came here with my mom to go seee Nachi Falls. Unfortunately, winter is the worst time of year to see a waterfall since it's so dry, but the town of Nachi Katsuura, where we stayed, was a nice and peaceful coastal town.
Tottori is somewhere that I've wanted to go for a long time and I'm happy I was able to go.

Okayama was more of a place I stopped over to get from Fukuoka to Naoshima, and then from Naoshima to Tottori. I think Okayama City is a good day trip, had lots of statues, interesting building, and a castle on dark mode.
